The paper proposes a neural network model for the task of story ending prediction, which involves understanding the story and sometimes requires commonsense knowledge. This task is closely related to natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category, as it covers topics related to natural language processing, including text classification, sentiment analysis, and language modeling. The proposed model in this paper involves sentence modeling and semantic representation, which are relevant to this sub-category. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category, as the paper proposes a machine learning model for a specific task. This sub-category covers topics related to machine learning, including neural networks, deep learning, and reinforcement learning. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category, as it covers topics related to the design and analysis of machine learning algorithms. The proposed model in this paper involves neural network architecture and training, which are relevant to this sub-category. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely sub-category, but still relevant as it covers topics related to neural networks and their applications. The proposed model in this paper involves a novel neural network architecture, which could be of interest to researchers in this sub-category.
